text: Went Here For Dinner As The Reviews Were Good Was Extremely Disappointed If Your Looking For Mexican Food This Is Not The Place To Come It Is Very Gourmet And Overpriced My Husband Ordered Santa Maria Tri Tip With Pinto Beans These Were Sweet Baked Beans Small Portion For 2400 I Order Half Chicken With Roasted Potatoes I Asked The Very Nice Waiter If The Sauce Was Sweet As It Mentioned It Had Apples In It He Said Absolutely Not So I Ordered This Item The Sauce Was Sweet It Was Pretty Much Apple Sauce On My Chicken Also About 2000 No Chips As Appetizers There Were The Pinwheel Doritos The Street Sellers Sell For A Dollar With Some Chili Pepper Sprinkled On Top Spent 6000 For 2 Meals 1 Beer Also Left Hungry And I Satisfied Would Not Recommend This Place Only Had A Few Appetizer And Salads And About 4 Dinner Entrees Not A Lot A Choices And Definitely Not Mexican There Was Not One Authentic Mexican Plate In The Menu

I Have Been To This Restaurant In Early 1980S And Last Time In 2003 When I Traveled Up The Coast I Remembered It As A Much Better Restaruant You Can Get Better Seafood At Dennys The Salmon Was Pretty Tasteless And Overcooked The Bread Was Excellent But The Meal Was Not It Is Dirty And Very Dated It Looks Like A Place For The Locals But Ive Heard There Are Better Places In Town Stay Away

I Ordered In For Delivery And Gave The Restaurant A Call At 836Pm At 930Pm Our Food Still Hadnt Arrived And I Was Given No Indication That Deliveries May Take Longer Than Expected I Called At 932Pm To Inquire About Our Order And I Was Told That Our Order Was Ready But The Driver Hadnt Returned To Pick It Up I Can Understand Its A Saturday And They Were Probably Busy But Knowing Our Food Was Sitting There Getting Colder By The Minute Because Of A Late Driver Was Not Comforting 955Pm And Still No Food So I Called The Restaurant To Cancel My Order I Told The Gentleman Or Lack Thereof On The Phone That I Wanted To Cancel My Order Because I Had Waited An Hour And A Half And Did Not Want To Wait For Cold Food He Tried To Persuade Me That The Food Was On Its Way And Was 5 Minutes Away I Kindly Declined And He Decided To Explain To A Fellow Employee That I Wanted To Cancel My Order Due To Waiting An Hour We Were Waiting An Hour And A Half He Then Transferred Me To Another Employee Who Gave Me A Hard Time About Cancelling My Order Seriously I Waited An Hour And A Half I Think It Was Completely Fair To Cancel An Order That No One Obviously Cared About The Inconsideration And Lack Of Professionalism I Received From The Staff And This Restaurant Was Enough To Prevent Me From Never Ordering From This Place Again Goodbye Ming Dynasty
